<div id="tricks_basic_box">
  <h1><strong>BASIC TRICKS</strong></h1>
  <hr>
  <h2>
    These are some of the basic movement optomizations that one MUST master if they are to ever speedrun OoT:
    <ul class="tricks_basic_movement_ul">
      <li>Correct rolling technique</li>
      <li>Fast swimming</li>
      <li>Back walking</li>
      <li>Side hopping</li>
    </ul>
    I find this video to be extremely helpful if any of these optimizations are foreign to you. This is an older video, but it is very short and delivers only the necessary information, it is very underrated in my opinion, but it might
    be because these techniques are known by most casual players of the game.
    <br>
    <a class="tricks_hyperlink_out" href="https://youtu.be/vFhDz-3wr3k">OoT Speedrunning 101 #1 - Basic Movement Techniques - aleckermit</a></h2>
    <iframe width="550" height="420" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/vFhDz-3wr3k"></iframe>
  </h2>
  <hr>
  <h2>
    These are some more of the basic optimizations, but they are more situational, and less about direct movement:
    <ul class="tricks_basic_movement_ul">
      <li>Shield dropping</li>
      <li>Power crouch stabbing</li>
      <li>Infinite Sword Glitch (ISG)
        <ul>
          <li>One of THE MOST USEFUL tricks</li>
          <li>Worth noting, the only way to draw sword without losing ISG is to draw it during a backflip</li>
        </ul></li>
      <li>Ground jumps
        <ul>
          <li>This is not used as much in current runs</li>
          <li>Can still be useful for back-up strategies and improvising</li>
        </ul></li>
      <li>Mega flip
        <ul>
          <li>Things are starting to get tricky here</li>
          <li>This requires practice and excelent timing</li>
        </ul></li>
      <li>Mega jump
        <ul>
          <li>This is more for things thath are out of reach due to being above Link's head</li>
          <li>This is a bit easier than Mega flip, but does require
              <a class="tricks_hyperlink_out" href="http://oot-speedruns.wikia.com/wiki/Frame_Rate_and_Pause_Buffering">"frame buffering"</a></li>
        </ul></li>
      <li>Hover boosting</li>
    </ul>
    Here is another helpful video, and will show step by step how to perform each trick and the necessary conditions. It is short and to the point, but some of
    these tricks are starting to become <a class="tricks_hyperlink_out" href="http://oot-speedruns.wikia.com/wiki/Frame_Rate_and_Pause_Buffering">"frame perfect"</a>.
    <br>
    <a class="tricks_hyperlink_out" href="https://youtu.be/zEM3GDxPkVc">OoT Speedrunning 101 #2 - Basic Movement Techniques - aleckermit</a></h2>
    <iframe width="550" height="420" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/zEM3GDxPkVc"></iframe>
  </h2>
</div>

