<div id="tricks_advanced_box">
  <h1><strong>ADVANCED TRICKS</strong></h1>
  <hr>
  <h2><i>NOTE: Tactics updated here constantly, be sure to check back!</i></h2>
  <h2>
    These are some more advanced techniques, that will require some of the basic skills, mainly ISG. They will require a lot of practice, are often
        <a class="tricks_hyperlink_out" href="http://oot-speedruns.wikia.com/wiki/Frame_Rate_and_Pause_Buffering">"frame perfect"</a>, and have multiple
        steps. Do not give up! They are rather simple and with practice you will be doing them like a pro in no time!
  </h2>
  <hr>
  <h2>
    <strong><a class="tricks_hyperlink_out" href="https://youtu.be/myqD82UZP60?t=2m46s">Bombchu hovering as an Adult</a><strong>
    <br>
    This is a very essential technique to master, as any run that allows glitches will use it, a lot. It can be used to reach alomst ANY area in the game; so yeah,
        it is pretty useful. The basic steps are as follows:
    <ol id="tricks_bombchu_hover_ol" style="text-align: left">
      <li>Get ISG while wearing the hover boots</li>
      <li>Back walk to the edge of a drop-off</li>
      <li>Do a backflip, and then press the bombchu AND shield buttons at <i>almost</i> the same time, making sure to press the bombchu button first</li>
      <li>Once the bombchu is finished exploding, you can let go of the shield button</li>
      <li>From here, the process can be repeated until you run out of bombchus or wish to quit, and you no longer need to use the
            <a class="tricks_hyperlink_out" href="http://supersmashbros.wikia.com/wiki/Z_button">"Z"</a> button</li>
      <li>When you would like to stop govering, all you need to do is swing your sword, or side hop or backflip for a little extra distance</li>
    </ol>
    <a class="tricks_hyperlink_out" href="https://youtu.be/myqD82UZP60?t=2m46s">OoT Speedrunning 101 #3 - Advanced Tricks and Glitches - aleckermit</a></h2>
    <iframe width="550" height="420" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/myqD82UZP60?start=166"></iframe>
  </h2>
